"{\"uid\": \"rappler.com-sports-football-argentina-coach-decries-circus-chaotic-morocco-opening-loss-paris-olympics-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  SUMMARY  This is AI generated summarization, which may have errors.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 69, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19, \"end\": 21, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9001937819022194, \"rank\": 0.11087192412139654, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For context, always refer to the full article.\", \"from\": 70, \"to\": 116, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"CONTROVERSIAL.\", \"from\": 118, \"to\": 132, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Giuliano Simeone of Argentina reacts during their men's football Group B match against Morocco in the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 133, \"to\": 250, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 133, \"end\": 149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diego_Simeone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Giuliano Simeone\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diego_Simeone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diego_Simeone\"}, {\"begin\": 153, \"end\": 162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.64310537215577e-17, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 198, \"end\": 205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_FIFA_World_Cup_Group_B\", \"score\": 0.9999999999122338, \"rank\": 8.574786726297434e-11, \"text\": \"Group B\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_FIFA_World_Cup_Group_B\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_FIFA_World_Cup_Group_B\"}, {\"begin\": 220, \"end\": 227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999636202, \"rank\": 3.6459290099861056e-11, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thaier Al-Sudani/REUTERS  PARIS, France - Argentina coach Javier Mascherano said he had never witnessed such a circus after a pitch invasion triggered a dramatic and long-delayed climax to the country's 2-1 loss to Morocco in their Olympic opener in St-Etienne on Wednesday, July 24.\", \"from\": 252, \"to\": 535, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 285, \"end\": 291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.323823116829268e-25, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 294, \"end\": 303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.64310537215577e-17, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 310, \"end\": 327, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Javier_Mascherano\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Javier Mascherano\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Javier_Mascherano\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Javier_Mascherano\"}, {\"begin\": 467, \"end\": 474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999636202, \"rank\": 3.6459290099861056e-11, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cristian Medina thought he had salvaged a 2-2 draw for Argentina when he scored deep into injury time, but the goal was ruled out for offside by VAR when play resumed for a few minutes after a two-hour stoppage to clear the stadium of fans.\", \"from\": 537, \"to\": 777, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 537, \"end\": 552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cristian_Medina\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cristian Medina\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cristian_Medina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cristian_Medina\"}, {\"begin\": 592, \"end\": 601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.64310537215577e-17, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 682, \"end\": 685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Video_assistant_referee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5442913024649958e-44, \"text\": \"VAR\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Video_assistant_referee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Video_assistant_referee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mascherano said there had been a lack of communication from organizers about what was going to happen as the team sat in the Geoffroy Guichard stadium dressing room before the resumption.\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 966, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I can not explain what happened.\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 1001, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We spent about an hour and a half in the dressing room where they never told us what was going to happen,\\\" Mascherano told reporters.\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1135, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Moroccan captains did not want to play, we did not want to continue, and fans threw things at us.\", \"from\": 1137, \"to\": 1239, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1142, \"end\": 1150, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999997844498, \"rank\": 2.154768514224142e-10, \"text\": \"Moroccan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the biggest circus I have ever seen in my life, I do not know why they spent an hour and 20 minutes reviewing a play.\", \"from\": 1240, \"to\": 1362, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If there is offside in Medina's goal, let the game go on with the momentum we have, I do not think the game should be played for three minutes after an hour and a half.\\\"\", \"from\": 1364, \"to\": 1534, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1388, \"end\": 1394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Medina\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.921793673106986e-26, \"text\": \"Medina\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Medina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Medina\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the former Argentina defensive midfielder said he did not want to indulge in excessive complaining and had encouraged his team to focus on their upcoming Group B fixtures against Iraq and Ukraine.\", \"from\": 1536, \"to\": 1741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1556, \"end\": 1565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.64310537215577e-17, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1699, \"end\": 1706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_FIFA_World_Cup_Group_B\", \"score\": 0.9999999999122338, \"rank\": 8.574786726297434e-11, \"text\": \"Group B\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_FIFA_World_Cup_Group_B\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_FIFA_World_Cup_Group_B\"}, {\"begin\": 1724, \"end\": 1728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iraq_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6013060952502678e-15, \"text\": \"Iraq\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iraq_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iraq_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1733, \"end\": 1740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8074225584006286e-18, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's no use complaining, we do not like this kind of thing to happen but we have to turn the page, look for positive things and we will look for the two victories we need to qualify.\\\"\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1927, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Argentina next faces Iraq in Lyon on Saturday, July 27.\", \"from\": 1929, \"to\": 1984, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1929, \"end\": 1938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.64310537215577e-17, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1950, \"end\": 1954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iraq_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6013060952502678e-15, \"text\": \"Iraq\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iraq_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iraq_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1958, \"end\": 1962, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympique_Lyonnais\", \"score\": 0.999999999364718, \"rank\": 6.355086877608371e-10, \"text\": \"Lyon\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympique_Lyonnais\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympique_Lyonnais\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Argentina's Cristian Medina scored deep in injury time to salvage what looked like a 2-2 draw, but the decision ruling out the goal for offside was delivered about two hours after play was suspended.\", \"from\": 1986, \"to\": 2185, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1986, \"end\": 1995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.64310537215577e-17, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1998, \"end\": 2013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cristian_Medina\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cristian Medina\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cristian_Medina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cristian_Medina\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After order was restored in Saint-Etienne and the teams had left the field following the fan invasion, they discovered that the match had not been completed but suspended by officials.\", \"from\": 2187, \"to\": 2371, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2215, \"end\": 2228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metz_Cathedral\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2200850670446695e-18, \"text\": \"Saint-Etienne\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q1370598\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metz_Cathedral\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metz_Cathedral\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The venue manager told Reuters the game had been interrupted, adding that a decision about whether the match would be completed was being discussed.\", \"from\": 2373, \"to\": 2521, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2396, \"end\": 2403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.14664368425786e-13, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The teams re-emerged on to the pitch to finish the match in an empty stadium, playing for three minutes and 15 seconds after VAR completed its review and disallowed the goal.\", \"from\": 2523, \"to\": 2697, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2648, \"end\": 2651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Video_assistant_referee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5442913024649958e-44, \"text\": \"VAR\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Video_assistant_referee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Video_assistant_referee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not remember something like this happening at this level, that the match is suspended for an hour and a half, warming up for 10 minutes and then play three,\\\" said Argentina manager Javier Mascherano.\", \"from\": 2699, \"to\": 2904, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2868, \"end\": 2877, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.64310537215577e-17, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2886, \"end\": 2903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Javier_Mascherano\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Javier Mascherano\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Javier_Mascherano\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Javier_Mascherano\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What happened on the pitch was a scandal, it's not a neighborhood tournament, it's the Olympics.\\\"\", \"from\": 2906, \"to\": 3004, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers later said they were working with stakeholders to understand the causes of the pitch invasion and determine appropriate measures.\", \"from\": 3006, \"to\": 3146, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Soufiane Rahimi scored twice for Morocco, the second goal from the penalty spot early in the second half, before Giuliano Simeone pulled one back for the 2004 and 2008 gold medallists in the 68th minute.\", \"from\": 3148, \"to\": 3351, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3148, \"end\": 3163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soufiane_Rahimi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Soufiane Rahimi\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soufiane_Rahimi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soufiane_Rahimi\"}, {\"begin\": 3181, \"end\": 3188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999636202, \"rank\": 3.6459290099861056e-11, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3261, \"end\": 3277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diego_Simeone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Giuliano Simeone\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diego_Simeone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diego_Simeone\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Host France later made a good start to their tournament in Marseille with two goals in eight minutes after the hour mark and a late header from Loic Bade gave them a comfortable 3-0 win over the United States.\", \"from\": 3353, \"to\": 3562, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3358, \"end\": 3364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.323823116829268e-25, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3412, \"end\": 3421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympique_de_Marseille\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.063038706902003e-15, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympique_de_Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympique_de_Marseille\"}, {\"begin\": 3502, \"end\": 3506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bade_District\", \"score\": 0.9999408043718064, \"rank\": 5.919892389525774e-05, \"text\": \"Bade\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bade_District\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bade_District\"}, {\"begin\": 3548, \"end\": 3561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999994205169829, \"rank\": 5.794831411613282e-07, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Captain Alexandre Lacazette sent a big crowd wild with a superb long-range effort to open the scoring before a fine strike from Michael Olise doubled the lead for Thierry Henry's side.\", \"from\": 3564, \"to\": 3748, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3572, \"end\": 3591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandre_Lacazette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alexandre Lacazette\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandre_Lacazette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandre_Lacazette\"}, {\"begin\": 3692, \"end\": 3705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Olise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Michael Olise\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Olise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Olise\"}, {\"begin\": 3727, \"end\": 3740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thierry_Henry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thierry Henry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thierry_Henry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thierry_Henry\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After the drama in St-Etienne, organizers will have been relieved that Israel's Group D opener against Mali at the Parc des Princes in Paris passed off without incident.\", \"from\": 3750, \"to\": 3919, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3821, \"end\": 3827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999054126, \"rank\": 9.364478009463166e-11, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3853, \"end\": 3857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5386926743258532e-19, \"text\": \"Mali\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3885, \"end\": 3890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.705567267349632e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 1-1 draw was played amid tight security because of heightened geopolitical tensions.\", \"from\": 3921, \"to\": 4009, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Diallo Hamidou's own goal put Israel ahead 11 minutes after the break but Doumbia Cheickna equalised for the African side with a fine header in the 63rd minute.\", \"from\": 4011, \"to\": 4171, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4011, \"end\": 4017, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Killing_of_Amadou_Diallo\", \"score\": 0.9999995841722876, \"rank\": 4.1581758747725135e-07, \"text\": \"Diallo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Killing_of_Amadou_Diallo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Killing_of_Amadou_Diallo\"}, {\"begin\": 4041, \"end\": 4047, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999054126, \"rank\": 9.364478009463166e-11, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier at the same venue, Spain beat Uzbekistan, 2-1, in the opening match of Group C despite struggling to hit their stride in the opening stages of the game.\", \"from\": 4173, \"to\": 4333, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4200, \"end\": 4205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.079368500419844e-28, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4211, \"end\": 4221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uzbekistan_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999998899511, \"rank\": 1.0998920976528922e-10, \"text\": \"Uzbekistan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uzbekistan_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uzbekistan_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4252, \"end\": 4259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_Euro_2012_Group_C\", \"score\": 0.9999997621166868, \"rank\": 2.3768472358324315e-07, \"text\": \"Group C\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_Euro_2012_Group_C\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_Euro_2012_Group_C\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Spaniards, silver medalists three years ago in Tokyo, took the lead in the 29th minute against Uzbekistan with a close-range finish from Marc Pubill.\", \"from\": 4335, \"to\": 4488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4339, \"end\": 4348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"score\": 0.9999886043746228, \"rank\": 1.1371768944432105e-05, \"text\": \"Spaniards\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\"}, {\"begin\": 4386, \"end\": 4391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999903152598237, \"rank\": 9.684825669039755e-06, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia